Leet Code 55 -- Jump Game 
  Find if we can reach last element from any element. 
  Check each element from last and if we find one then we check if we can reach that element from previous elements.
  
  Eventually we reach index 0,
  or
  We reach an index (say x) for which there is no element (say y) from which we can reach x, 
  such that index of y is less than index of x.

  If we do not reach till index 0, we can never reach the end element by starting at 0th index.


class Solution {
    public boolean canJump(int[] nums) {
        if(nums.length==1)
            return true;
        int posToReach=nums.length-1;
        for(int i=nums.length-2;i>=0;i--){
            if(nums[i]>=((posToReach)-i)){
                posToReach=i;
            }
        }
        return posToReach==0;
    }
}
